      "writtenOn": "2019-02-04T14:30:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Here we\u0027re going back down to uint16_t, which is what\u0027s triggering the issue. This code:\n\nTakes a 565 value and shifts just the green bits by 16. That produces a 32-bit value that looks like: 00000GGGGGG00000 RRRRR000000BBBBB\n\nThen it does the mip-mapping math, taking advantage of the 0s in the overflow region of each channel. Finally, it squashes that 32-bit filtered value back into 16 bits, by shifting the green bits back into position. The mask for the R+B bits is just ~0b1111100000011111, which leaves all of the green bits in the top half.",
      "parentUuid": "5125ad3b_d3e7d966",
      "revId": "f9e7144c41bff21ca22b825d2d2019fcf4bc9ada",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
